At temperatures above the tri-critical point (red), the transition from the isotropic metal to the spin-triplet nematic (green region) is continuous. Below the tri-critical point, fluctuations render the phase 
transition first order and stabilize a region of spatially modulated, helical spin-triplet nematic order with ordering wave vector ${\bm q} = q/\sqrt{2} \,(1,\pm1,0)$ 
(blue region). The transitions between the modulated and homogeneous states is continuous, but would become weakly first-order in the presence of magnetic 
